main event: A civilian observed a sharply outlined, light or gas-like object fading out in sections while setting in the west on December 14, 1964 in Falls Church, Virginia.
interesting points: The object appeared to be extremely large.
The object was distorted by the atmospheric conditions and the witness did not observe any physical details.
The object was seen setting in the west, starting in the 1st quarter on December 14 and fully on December 19.
The witness did not expect the object as it just appeared and was looking in that direction.
The report includes photographs of the sighting, but the image provided does not contain any photographs.
sighted object: a sharply outlined, light or gas-like object
